            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "This still needs to be present as the current published version (~2 years ago) of `vscode-langservers-extracted` assumes it exists and fails otherwise while trying to get the value inside it. Current version of `vscode-eslint` doesn't seem to have this issue.",
            "commit_id": "770ffa95d1c0f6dfb3b3e5987ff872130c201c84",
            "created_at": "2026-02-27T05:11:11Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -129,9 +147,7 @@ return {\n     ---@diagnostic disable-next-line: assign-type-mismatch\n     packageManager = nil,\n     useESLintClass = false,\n-    experimental = {\n-      useFlatConfig = false,\n-    },\n+    experimental = {},",
